This directory should contain example python programs.

For an execellent introduction to Python see:
http://docs.python.org/2/tutorial/introduction.html

This activity was spun off as Python is widely used in introductory
courses to electrical engineering and computer sceience.
See: http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/electrical-engineering-and-computer-science/6-01sc-introduction-to-electrical-engineering-and-computer-science-i-spring-2011/Syllabus/

Python comes with IDLE, a graphical program editing environment. 
There is some effort to make this work on cygwin, reverting to using Emacs...